# Git commit identity (SmartSlab)

Do **not** run `git config --global` or `git config` to change identity.

For every `git commit` in this repository, pass author via per-command flags:

```bash
git -c user.name="Juan Cruz" -c user.email="juansiestadisponible@gmail.com" commit -m "..."
```

- **Name:** Juan Cruz
- **Email:** juansiestadisponible@gmail.com
- **Remote:** https://github.com/jcruzrivera/SmartSlab.app

On PowerShell (no heredoc), use multiple `-m` flags or a here-string for the message body.

Never use placeholder identities such as `dev@smartslab.local` or `SmartSlab Dev`.
